<item>
            <title>[HBASE-2855] Command line switch to specify the HBaseMaster to connect to</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/HBASE-2855</link>
                <project id="12310753" key="HBASE">HBase</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;The HBase Shell wiki page &lt;a href=&quot;http://wiki.apache.org/hadoop/Hbase/Shell&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow&quot;&gt;http://wiki.apache.org/hadoop/Hbase/Shell&lt;/a&gt; states that there is a command line switch &lt;tt&gt;--master=MASTER&lt;/tt&gt; to specify a remote hbase master to connect to. This command line option does, however, not exist. Instead, in order to connect to a remote cluster, the user has to overwrite the shell variable &lt;tt&gt;$HBASE_CONFIG_DIR&lt;/tt&gt; with the path to the remote cluster&apos;s configuration files that have to be locally available.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;A command line switch would be better suited for this, since the user/developer then would not have to write a XML config script.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
